<div id="content">        <div class="spacer"></div>             <span id="shash-97734"><div class="post" id="post-97734">                    <h1><a href="http://trilema.com/2020/a-tale-of-nothingness/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to A tale of nothingness">A tale of nothingness</a></h1>                        <div class="date">                                     Saturday, 07 November, Year 12 d.Tr.&nbsp;|&nbsp;Author: <a href="http://trilema.com/author/admin/" title="Posts by Mircea Popescu">Mircea Popescu</a>                                                        </div>

                        <div class="entry">
<p style="text-align: right;"><strong>Motto :</strong> Du’ su’ u pudendu,<br />
 cu avu assà e cu avu <strong>nudu</strong>.</p>
<p>The motto is a rather old proverb, here rendered in Sicilian (which is itself rather old a language, neither particularly original nor all that authentic to the historic Kingdom [of the two Sicilies], but more in the vein of a preserved Legionnaire's vernacular). What it says is that there's two kinds of powerful : the kind that has plenty, and the kind that has... nothing.</p>
<p><strong>Nudu</strong>l is, of course, how you say the nude<sup><a href="#footnote_0_97734" id="identifier_0_97734" class="footnote-link footnote-identifier-link" title="Not the nude as in the substantivation of herds without clothes, `the nude crowded on the beach` ; but the nude as in `Joan of Michigan is a nude statuary depiction of America's Greatness (such as it is). The nude was thought lost since the discovery of the West Indies however bla bla bla`.">i</a></sup> in Romanian (itself very much not a language in any proper sense, but merely the still-warm core of Latin somewhat crusted over but otherwise <a href="http://trilema.com/2019/din-togo-din-togo-da-de-a-cui/#footnote_1_83953">kept safe</a> inside). It is also phonetically very close to the Spanish <strong>nada</strong>, which is how you say nothing in that language.</p>
<p><strong>Nada</strong> is not how you say nothing in Romanian, however. <strong>Nada</strong> is how you say <em>the lure</em> in Romanian, which circumstance should suffice to illustrate and circumscribe the confused <a href="http://trilema.com/2020/babydoll-and-platonic-ideals/">Platonism</a> of "<a href="http://trilema.com/2011/europa-crestina-si-alte-aberatii/">the christian core of European culture</a>" : a lure is definitionally not what it seems, but <em>less</em>. The <a href="http://trilema.com/2018/the-man-versus-the-state/?b=inherent&#038;e=socialism#select">bait</a> can't possibly be what it seems to be, it has to be cheaper for the substitution to make sense. <em>Therefore we might as well say it's not worth nothing at all</em>. Nudity, of course, is the ultimate lure<sup><a href="#footnote_1_97734" id="identifier_1_97734" class="footnote-link footnote-identifier-link" title="The Romanian expression being `ti-a placut sa dai din craci, acu' leagana si taci`, although I'm sure you've got your own.">ii</a></sup> ; the rest just follows from here, through <a href="http://trilema.com/2017/zuleika-dobson-or-an-proper-love-story/?b=said%20for%20convention&#038;e=common#select">linguistic logic</a>.</p>
<p>So forget both <a href="http://trilema.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/lagonie_1902_elagabalus_conduisant_un_char_a_seize_chevaux_blancs_ou_sur_un_autel_de_pierreries_reposait_le_cone_de_pierre_noire.jpg">heroic</a><sup><a href="#footnote_2_97734" id="identifier_2_97734" class="footnote-link footnote-identifier-link" title="Stonedick-worshipping tranny emperor, with whores and horses.">iii</a></sup> and <a href="http://trilema.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/siemiradzki_christian_dirce.jpg">pathetic</a><sup><a href="#footnote_3_97734" id="identifier_3_97734" class="footnote-link footnote-identifier-link" title="Early xtian asshat shown dead alongside the bull that had just ravished her precious virginity, for the serious offense of having attempted to mother up the joint.
Back then they still tried.">iv</a></sup> nudity, forget <a href="http://trilema.com/2020/a-full-deck-of-beach-cards/#beach-33">the obligations</a> incumbent upon female existence, never mind any of that. It's "nothing", you know. Take <a href="http://trilema.com/2020/the-journall-of-the-good-mr-archibald-pizdys-as-laid-in-his-own-hand-for-the-year-of-our-king-charles-19th-week-12/?b=I%20set%20her&#038;e=it#select">the $42</a> worth of <del datetime="2020-11-07T12:34:21+00:00">beads</del> <a href="http://trilema.com/2013/the-endless-story-of-korea/?b=Plaintiff&#038;e=untenable#select">leaves</a> an'... <a href="http://trilema.com/2016/asscience/">leave</a>. Quietly. Don't make <a href="http://trilema.com/2015/strategy-for-the-antisocial-struggle/">a fuss</a>, above all don't make <a href="http://trilema.com/2016/the-story-of-elliot-rodger-by-elliot-rodger-adnotated-part-eight/?b=Day%20of&#038;e=Retribution#select">a fuss</a><sup><a href="#footnote_4_97734" id="identifier_4_97734" class="footnote-link footnote-identifier-link" title="Why would you make a fuss over nothing ?! Maybe you're bad at math, or something ? There are ways to help you trebuie sa intelegi ca, you know.">v</a></sup>. </p>
<p>PS. To make the title... whole : the motto is actually "du’ su’ i putenti<sup><a href="#footnote_5_97734" id="identifier_5_97734" class="footnote-link footnote-identifier-link" title="Do you remember what pudenda means, by the way ?">vi</a></sup>, cu avi assà e cu nun avi nenti", meaning there's no actual substance to this article (beyond your unyielding, inexhaustible capacity for directed dreaming).</p>
&mdash;&mdash;&mdash;<ol class="footnotes"><li id="footnote_0_97734" class="footnote">Not <em>the nude</em> as in the substantivation of herds without clothes, "<a href="http://trilema.com/2019/thelastpsychiatristcom-are-all-drug-reps-hot-adnotated/?b=predictor&#038;e=suicide#select">the nude</a> crowded on the beach" ; but <em>the nude</em> as in "Joan of Michigan is a nude statuary depiction of America's Greatness (such as it is). The nude was thought lost since the discovery of the West Indies however bla bla bla". [<a href="#identifier_0_97734" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_1_97734" class="footnote">The Romanian expression being "ti-a placut sa dai din craci, acu' leagana si taci", although I'm sure you've <a href="http://trilema.com/2015/prophylaxis/">got your own</a>. [<a href="#identifier_1_97734" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_2_97734" class="footnote"><a href="http://trilema.com/2011/erotoghid-pentru-femeia-adulta/?b=penisul%20erect&#038;e=limitat#select">Stonedick</a>-worshipping tranny emperor, with whores and horses. [<a href="#identifier_2_97734" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_3_97734" class="footnote">Early xtian asshat shown dead alongside the bull that had just ravished her precious virginity, for the serious offense of having attempted to <a href="http://trilema.com/2019/the-slut-and-the-whore/">mother up</a> the joint.</p>
<p>Back then they still tried. [<a href="#identifier_3_97734" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_4_97734" class="footnote">Why would you make a</span> fuss over <em>nothing</em> ?! Maybe you're <a href="http://trilema.com/2019/thelastpsychiatristcom-bad-at-math-adnotated/">bad at math</a>, or something ? There are ways to help you <a href="http://trilema.com/2020/dumb-bitches-giving-prostitution-a-bad-name/?b=trebuie%20sa&#038;e=intelegi#select">trebuie sa intelegi ca</a>, you know. [<a href="#identifier_4_97734" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li><li id="footnote_5_97734" class="footnote">Do you remember what <em>pudenda</em> means, by the way ? [<a href="#identifier_5_97734" class="footnote-link footnote-back-link">&#8617;</a>]</li></ol>
              <div>
                <div class="alignleft">&laquo; <a href="http://trilema.com/2020/and-i-dont-think-meron-is-fucking-kidding-either/">And I don't think Meron is fucking kidding, either.</a></div>
                <div class="alignright"><a href="http://trilema.com/2020/babydoll-and-the-facts-of-life/">Babydoll and the facts of life</a> &raquo;</div>
              </div>

